{
  "texts": [
    "Such architecture enables a high degree of parallelization, which allows the model to train on much larger datasets than before, retain exponentially more parameters, and capture long-range dependencies in the data to thereby intelligently comprehend language contexts.",
    "Image generation models are deep learning models that can generate images from text prompts.",
    "Early models began to be developed in the mid-2010s, with notable advancements made by generative adversarial networks and variational autoencoders, which reconstruct images from sampled white noise.",
    "More recent advancements include GenAI based in diffusion models, a class of generative models inspired by thermodynamics that adopt a unique approach to image generation by gradually adding noise to an image until it becomes completely degraded (Ho et al., 2020).",
    "The ability to train GenAI models on an organization's existing knowledge offers an opportunity to harness the extensive collective expertise shared among employees as well as insights from customers and stakeholders."
  ]
}